snippet: Partial results for national elections in the Central African Republic showed that there had been a high voter turnout and that two candidates were running neck in neck.
abstract: Partial ballot count in Central African Republic presidential election shows high voter turnout and Anicet-Georges Dologuele with slight lead over Faustin Archange Touadera.
lead_paragraph: Partial results for national elections in the Central African Republic showed that there had been a high voter turnout and that two candidates were running neck in neck.

headline.main: Central African Republic: Two Presidential Candidates Are Almost Tied
headline.print_headline: Africa; Central African Republic: Election Turnout Is High; Two Presidential Candidates Are Almost Tied
